Commentary Text: Mishra to Watson, wide, out Stumped!! That is the experience of Mishra. He loaded it up with a flight and kept it away from Watson's range - outside off, the Australian still tries to whack it over extra cover, but is done in by the turn. The back foot is dragged out and by the time he tries to get back, Pant had light up the stumps. The foot was on the line and it is an easy call for the TV umpire.
